The paper discusses a variant of cuckoo hashing, which is a data structure used in computer science for efficient storage and retrieval of data. The paper focuses on improving memory utilization and insertion time, which are key concerns in data storage and retrieval. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Other likely sub-categories include cs.DB (Databases), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as these sub-categories are also relevant to the topic of data storage and retrieval.
